om\": 1981, \"to\": 2005, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You respected each other, even if your countries are divided by war and conflict.\", \"from\": 2006, \"to\": 2087, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"your countries\", \"from\": 2040, \"to\": 2054}, {\"ngram\": \"war\", \"from\": 2070, \"to\": 2073}, {\"ngram\": \"conflict\", \"from\": 2078, \"to\": 2086}]}, {\"sentence\": \"You created a culture of peace.\", \"from\": 2088, \"to\": 2119, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a culture\", \"from\": 2100, \"to\": 2109}, {\"ngram\": \"peace\", \"from\": 2113, \"to\": 2118}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This inspired all of us and billions of people around the globe.\", \"from\": 2119, \"to\": 2184, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 2141, \"to\": 2143}, {\"ngram\": \"billions\", \"from\": 2148, \"to\": 2156}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 2160, \"to\": 2166}, {\"ngram\": \"the globe\", \"from\": 2174, \"to\": 2183}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thank you for making us dream.\", \"from\": 2185, \"to\": 2215, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 2206, \"to\": 2208}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thank you for making us believe in a better world for everyone.\", \"from\": 2216, \"to\": 2279, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 2237, \"to\": 2239}, {\"ngram\": \"a better world\", \"from\": 2251, \"to\": 2265}, {\"ngram\": \"everyone\", \"from\": 2270, \"to\": 2278}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We know that the Olympic Games cannot create peace.\", \"from\": 2279, \"to\": 2331, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games\", \"from\": 2293, \"to\": 2310}, {\"ngram\": \"peace\", \"from\": 2325, \"to\": 2330}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the Olympic Games can create a culture of peace that inspires the world.\", \"from\": 2332, \"to\": 2408, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games\", \"from\": 2336, \"to\": 2353}, {\"ngram\": \"a culture\", \"from\": 2365, \"to\": 2374}, {\"ngram\": \"peace\", \"from\": 2378, \"to\": 2383}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 2398, \"to\": 2407}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This is why I call on everyone who shares this Olympic spirit: let us live this culture of peace every single day.\", \"from\": 2409, \"to\": 2523, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"everyone\", \"from\": 2431, \"to\": 2439}, {\"ngram\": \"this Olympic spirit\", \"from\": 2451, \"to\": 2470}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 2476, \"to\": 2478}, {\"ngram\": \"this culture\", \"from\": 2484, \"to\": 2496}, {\"ngram\": \"peace\", \"from\": 2500, \"to\": 2505}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There was also special praise for the 45,000 volunteers who assisted during the Games, which began with a rain-soaked opening ceremony along the Seine on 26 July.As well as reflecting on the Olympics in Paris, the closing ceremony provided a showcase for Los Angeles, which will host the Games for a third time in 2028.R&B artist H.E.R.\", \"from\": 2523, \"to\": 2860, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2669, \"end\": 2674, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999601211823673, \"rank\": 3.987747989151786e-05, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 2727, \"end\": 2732, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.556120703327853e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2779, \"end\": 2790, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.956721663598194e-14, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}, {\"begin\": 2854, \"end\": 2860, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/H.E.R.\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.8298089014042313e-35, \"text\": \"H.E.R.\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/H.E.R.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/H.E.R.\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"special praise\", \"from\": 2539, \"to\": 2553}, {\"ngram\": \"the 45,000 volunteers\", \"from\": 2558, \"to\": 2579}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 2600, \"to\": 2609}, {\"ngram\": \"a rain-soaked opening ceremony\", \"from\": 2628, \"to\": 2658}, {\"ngram\": \"26 July\", \"from\": 2678, \"to\": 2685}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 2711, \"to\": 2723}, {\"ngram\": \"the closing ceremony\", \"from\": 2734, \"to\": 2754}, {\"ngram\": \"a showcase\", \"from\": 2764, \"to\": 2774}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 2808, \"to\": 2817}, {\"ngram\": \"a third time\", \"from\": 2822, \"to\": 2834}, {\"ngram\": \"2028.R&B artist\", \"from\": 2838, \"to\": 2853}]}, {\"sentence\": \"performed the American national anthem inside Stade de France before viewers were transported to LA.Mountain biker Kate Courtney, track and field legend Michael Johnson and skateboarder Jagger Eaton took the Olympic flag on a tour of the city - visiting sites such as the Los Angeles Memorial Coliseum and Venice Beach - while Cruise was pictured in front of the iconic Hollywood sign, complete with Olympic rings.Rapper Snoop Dogg, who has been working as a special correspondent for American television network NBC during Paris 2024, performed alongside Dr Dre as part of a memorable finale that whetted the appetite for four years' time.00votesArticle Rating Actor Tom Cruise descended from the roof of Stade de France to collect the Olympic flag as part of the handover to the American city of Los Angeles, which will host the next Games in 2028, before departing on a motorcycle.\", \"from\": 2861, \"to\": 3746, \"entities\": [{\"begin\"